{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 00:29:57.939007", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary of Findings\n- Anomaly detected: Host pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2) exhibits loss of connectivity and inconsistent interface state. It cannot reach its default gateway or other hosts, and other hosts cannot reach it.\n- Fabric health: The EBGP-based Clos fabric (leaves, spines, super-spine) appears healthy. BGP sessions are established and routing tables are fully populated on the leaf routers. Host pc_0_0 is operating normally.\n- Fault localization: Issue is localized to the edge host pc_0_1 and/or its directly connected link to leaf_router_0_1 (interface eth8 on the leaf, eth0 on the host).\n- Probable root cause: pc_0_1’s interface eth0 is down or flapping and the host is missing a default route. When the interface is down, even on-link traffic (10.0.1.1) becomes unreachable, causing “Network is unreachable.” The missing default route further prevents off-subnet connectivity even when the interface is up.\n\nEvidence and Analysis\n1) Reachability symptoms\n- Global reachability test shows many hosts able to reach each other with 0% loss and low RTTs; however, any tests involving pc_0_1 have status unknown/unreachable.\n- Direct test:\n  - pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: ping timed out.\n  - pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0 or 10.0.1.1: “Network is unreachable” from pc_0_1, indicating no usable route/interface at the time of test.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 -> pc_0_1: ping succeeds but with anomalies (25% loss in one run; initial >1s RTT followed by ~1–2 ms), consistent with intermittent reachability and ARP resolution. Subsequent retry showed 0% loss but still an initial 1s RTT.\n\n2) Host pc_0_1 interface and routing\n- Interface state: Conflicting/unstable state observed.\n  - ip -d link show eth0 reported state DOWN at one point.\n  - Later ip -s link show eth0 reported state UP, LOWER_UP with RX/TX counters incrementing (but with RX drops).\n  - ethtool eth0: Link detected: no.\n  These indicate the link is either flapping or the driver reports no carrier intermittently; when the interface is down, the kernel rejects even on-link traffic as unreachable.\n- Addressing: ip addr shows 10.0.1.2/24 on eth0 as expected.\n- Routing: Only connected route exists: 10.0.1.0/24 dev eth0. No default route is present, unlike pc_0_0 which has “default via 10.0.0.1.” This means even if the interface is up, pc_0_1 cannot reach off-subnet destinations without a default route; however, the immediate “Network is unreachable” to 10.0.1.1 specifically happened when the interface was down.\n\n3) Leaf router 0_1 (10.0.1.1 on eth8)\n- Interface eth8 is UP, LOWER_UP with normal counters and ARP entry for pc_0_1:\n  - ARP: 10.0.1.2 lladdr fa:6d:6a:a6:6a:f9 STALE (expected for a quiet host).\n- BGP status is healthy:\n  - show ip bgp summary: 8 neighbors all Established, prefixes received as expected.\n- Routing table populated with all 10.x/24s via EBGP and connected 10.0.1.0/24 via eth8.\n\n4) Other host (pc_0_0) baseline\n- pc_0_0 has default route via 10.0.0.1 and behaves normally, supporting that the core fabric and its leaf are healthy.\n\nImpact Assessment\n- The outage is isolated to host pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2). The core routers and other hosts operate normally.\n- From the fabric perspective, the leaf can reach the host intermittently, indicating the leaf and L3 control-plane are not the source of the problem.\n\nRoot Cause Assessment\n- Primary: pc_0_1’s eth0 is down or flapping (as evidenced by ip link DOWN, ethtool reporting no link, intermittent ping success from the leaf). When the interface is down, the connected route is not usable, resulting in immediate “Network is unreachable” even to the on-link gateway.\n- Secondary configuration issue: pc_0_1 lacks a default route. This would prevent any off-subnet traffic even when the interface is up, contrasting with pc_0_0 which has a default route via its leaf.\n\nDevices Implicated\n- Faulty/affected device: pc_0_1 (host NIC eth0 and its local routing).\n- Network devices (leaf/spine/super-spine): No faults detected; BGP and routing tables are healthy; leaf_router_0_1’s host-facing interface is up and can reach the host at times.\n\nNo mitigation is proposed at this stage per request.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 19934, "output_tokens": 3275, "total_tokens": 23209, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 19456}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2176}}}
